<section id="command-circle">
<title>CIRCLE</title>
<indexterm><primary>CIRCLE</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>CIRCLE</command> <parameter>radius</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Draws a circle based on the turtle's position and the <parameter>radius</parameter> input.
The center-point of the circle is the turtle's current position.
CIRCLE does not move the turtle.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<para>
A 2D example:
<programlisting><userinput>CIRCLE 100</userinput>
</programlisting>
</para>

<para>
A 3D example:
<programlisting><userinput>PERSPECTIVE
REPEAT 36 [CIRCLE 100 RIGHTROLL 5]</userinput>
</programlisting>
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>See Also</term>
<listitem><simplelist>
<member><link linkend="command-circle2">CIRCLE2</link></member>
</simplelist></listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</section>
